snippet.textDisplay:
it would make sense to keep him

1. they have alot of holes they need filled(DL, WR, TE, OL, FB) leaving the QB saves time/money and continuity

2. Brady is still good. he has an arm that can throw 60+ (shown this season) is still the best reader of defenses in the NFL. protects the ball well. and is overall pretty accurate.

3. Brady already understands how to run the offense. the 2020 season wont be used to teach someone new and go through growing pains

4. hes cheap

5. hes the best free agent QB on the market right now.
